    "text": "Memory is the faculty of the mind by which data or information is encoded, stored, and retrieved when needed.",
    "topic": "Memory definition"
  },
  {
    "text": "Memory loss is usually described as forgetfulness or a disorder such as amnesia.",
    "topic": "Memory disorders"
  },
  {
    "text": "Memory is often understood as an information processing system with explicit and implicit functioning that includes a sensory processor, short-term (or working) memory, and long-term memory.",
    "topic": "Memory as information processing system"
  },
  {
    "text": "Declarative, or explicit memory, is the conscious storage and recollection of data, encompassing semantic and episodic memory.",
    "topic": "Declarative memory"
  },
  {
    "text": "Episodic memory refers to information that is encoded along a spatial and temporal framework.",
    "topic": "Episodic memory"
  }
]
